70class RtpVideoStreamReceiver : public LossNotificationSender,
71 public RecoveredPacketReceiver,

78 public:
79 // DEPRECATED due to dependency on ReceiveStatisticsProxy.
80 RtpVideoStreamReceiver(
81 Clock* clock,
82 Transport* transport,
83 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats,
84 // The packet router is optional; if provided, the RtpRtcp module for this
85 // stream is registered as a candidate for sending REMB and transport
86 // feedback.

88 const VideoReceiveStream::Config* config,
89 ReceiveStatistics* rtp_receive_statistics,
90 ReceiveStatisticsProxy* receive_stats_proxy,
91 ProcessThread* process_thread,
92 NackSender* nack_sender,
93 // The KeyFrameRequestSender is optional; if not provided, key frame
94 // requests are sent via the internal RtpRtcp module.
95 KeyFrameRequestSender* keyframe_request_sender,
96 OnCompleteFrameCallback* complete_frame_callback,
97 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
98 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer);

100 RtpVideoStreamReceiver(
101 Clock* clock,

103 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats,
104 // The packet router is optional; if provided, the RtpRtcp module for this

106 // feedback.

108 const VideoReceiveStream::Config* config,
109 ReceiveStatistics* rtp_receive_statistics,

188 // Optionally set a frame decryptor after a stream has started. This will not

190 void SetFrameDecryptor(
191 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor);
192
193 // Sets a frame transformer after a stream has started, if no transformer
194 // has previously been set. Does not reset the decoder state.

196 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer);

204 // RtpDemuxer only forwards a given RTP packet to one sink. However, some
205 // sinks, such as FlexFEC, might wish to be informed of all of the packets
206 // a given sink receives (or any set of sinks). They may do so by registering
207 // themselves as secondary sinks.
208 void AddSecondarySink(RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink);
209 void RemoveSecondarySink(const RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink);

211 private:
212 // Implements RtpVideoFrameReceiver.
213 void ManageFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) override;
214
215 // Used for buffering RTCP feedback messages and sending them all together.
216 // Note:
217 // 1. Key frame requests and NACKs are mutually exclusive, with the
218 // former taking precedence over the latter.
219 // 2. Loss notifications are orthogonal to either. (That is, may be sent
220 // alongside either.)
221 class RtcpFeedbackBuffer : public KeyFrameRequestSender,
222 public NackSender,
223 public LossNotificationSender {
224 public:
225 RtcpFeedbackBuffer(KeyFrameRequestSender* key_frame_request_sender,
226 NackSender* nack_sender,
227 LossNotificationSender* loss_notification_sender);
228
229 ~RtcpFeedbackBuffer() override = default;
230
231 // KeyFrameRequestSender implementation.
232 void RequestKeyFrame() RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_) override;
233
234 // NackSender implementation.
235 void SendNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers,
236 bool buffering_allowed) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_) override;
237
238 // LossNotificationSender implementation.
239 void SendLossNotification(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
240 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
241 bool decodability_flag,
242 bool buffering_allowed)
243 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_) override;
244
245 // Send all RTCP feedback messages buffered thus far.
246 void SendBufferedRtcpFeedback() RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_);
247
248 private:
249 // LNTF-related state.
250 struct LossNotificationState {
251 LossNotificationState(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
252 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
253 bool decodability_flag)
254 : last_decoded_seq_num(last_decoded_seq_num),
255 last_received_seq_num(last_received_seq_num),
256 decodability_flag(decodability_flag) {}
257
258 uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num;
259 uint16_t last_received_seq_num;
260 bool decodability_flag;
261 };
262 struct ConsumedRtcpFeedback {
263 bool request_key_frame = false;
264 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_sequence_numbers;
265 absl::optional<LossNotificationState> lntf_state;
266 };
267
268 ConsumedRtcpFeedback ConsumeRtcpFeedback() RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_);
269 ConsumedRtcpFeedback ConsumeRtcpFeedbackLocked()
270 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_);
271 // This method is called both with and without mutex_ held.
272 void SendRtcpFeedback(ConsumedRtcpFeedback feedback);
273
274 KeyFrameRequestSender* const key_frame_request_sender_;
275 NackSender* const nack_sender_;
276 LossNotificationSender* const loss_notification_sender_;
277
278 // NACKs are accessible from two threads due to nack_module_ being a module.
279 Mutex mutex_;
280
281 // Key-frame-request-related state.
282 bool request_key_frame_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
283
284 // NACK-related state.
285 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_sequence_numbers_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
286
287 absl::optional<LossNotificationState> lntf_state_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
288 };
